item.description: The main topics of this page are Wendell B’s cause of death and obituary information. Wendell is a Southern R&B singer who looks to Will Downing and Luther Vandross for vocal influence. Smoother musicians like Barry White and Bobby Womack are among his influences. Whether recording under his full name, as simply Wendell, or as Wendell B, the St. Louis, Missouri native has managed to keep the blues in R&B, in stark contrast to the vast bulk of commercial R&B that has been out since his early 1990s debut.
